---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import { SITE, url } from '../lib/site';
---
<BaseLayout title="About">
  <Hero
    eyebrow="About the camp"
    title="A focused week for the next generation of ML-for-health researchers"
    lead="The AHLI Health AI Summer Camp is a week-long intensive designed to give PhD students the rigor, tools, and community to do excellent machine learning for health."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Our goal</h2>
      <p>
        Machine learning for health sits between two demanding fields. Doing it
        well means understanding both the methods and the clinical realities they
        touch. The camp exists to help early-career researchers build that
        combined fluency in a concentrated, supportive setting.
      </p>
      <p>
        The week is hands-on by design. Concept sessions are paired with guided
        lab work, and the cohort is kept small enough — around 40 researchers —
        for genuine discussion and mentorship.
      </p>

      <h3>Who it's for</h3>
      <p>
        The camp is aimed at PhD students whose research involves machine
        learning for health (ML4H). Participants typically have a working
        foundation in machine learning and want to deepen their practice in the
        health setting specifically — data, evaluation, study design, and
        translation.
      </p>

      <h3>What makes it different</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Deliverable-driven.</strong> Every day produces a concrete artifact, not just notes.</li>
        <li><strong>Realistic data.</strong> Labs use synthetic clinical data modeled on MIMIC-IV structure.</li>
        <li><strong>Current methods.</strong> Coverage spans classical models through the foundation-model landscape.</li>
        <li><strong>Small cohort.</strong> Roughly 40 participants, for real conversation with instructors and peers.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout">
        <p>
          <strong>The Project Workbook.</strong> Each participant's daily
          deliverables accumulate into a single cohesive workbook. By the final
          day, you leave not only with new skills but with a structured reference
          you can bring back to your own research.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3>Support and partners</h3>
      <p>
        The camp is supported by the {SITE.funder} and co-located with
        {SITE.colocatedWith}, connecting participants to the wider health-AI
        research community.
      </p>

      <div class="btn-row">
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href={url('curriculum')}>Explore the curriculum</a>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={url('instructors')}>Meet the instructors</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
